    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Greetings: Hello"
        },
        "text": "The most common and universal greeting in Arabic is 'As-salamu alaykum'. It means 'Peace be upon you'. It can be used at any time of day.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "السلام عليكم",
            "english": "Hello / Peace be upon you",
            "transliteration": "As-salamu alaykum"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Greetings: Good morning"
        },
        "text": "To greet someone specifically in the morning, you can use 'Sabah al-khayr'. The response is 'Sabah an-noor'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "صباح الخير",
            "english": "Good morning",
            "transliteration": "Sabah al-khayr"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "صباح النور",
            "english": "Good morning (response, lit. Morning of light)",
            "transliteration": "Sabah an-noor"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Greetings: Good evening"
        },
        "text": "Similarly, for the evening, use 'Masa' al-khayr'. The response is 'Masa' an-noor'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "مساء الخير",
            "english": "Good evening",
            "transliteration": "Masa' al-khayr"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "مساء النور",
            "english": "Good evening (response, lit. Evening of light)",
            "transliteration": "Masa' an-noor"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
