      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'What is your name?' (male)"
        },
        "text": "To ask a male 'What is your name?', you use 'Ma ismuka?'. Note the 'fatḥa' (كَ) on the final letter indicating masculine gender.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ما اسمكَ؟",
            "english": "What is your name? (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Ma ismuká?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The 'fatḥa' on كَ indicates male."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'What is your name?' (female)"
        },
        "text": "To ask a female 'What is your name?', you use 'Ma ismuki?'. Note the 'kasra' (كِ) on the final letter indicating feminine gender.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ما اسمكِ؟",
            "english": "What is your name? (to a female)",
            "transliteration": "Ma ismuki?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The 'kasra' on كِ indicates female."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Stating 'My name is...'"
        },
        "text": "To state your name, you say 'Ismi...' followed by your name. The 'ي' (ya) at the end means 'my'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "اسمي أحمد.",
            "english": "My name is Ahmed.",
            "transliteration": "Ismi Ahmed."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "اسمي سارة.",
            "english": "My name is Sara.",
            "transliteration": "Ismi Sara."
          }
        ]
      }
